# GitHub Secrets Configuration for CI/CD Pipeline
# ================================================
# These variables should be configured as GitHub Secrets
# Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New repository secret

# === Docker Hub Credentials ===
# Required for pushing Docker images to registry
DOCKERHUB_USERNAME=your_dockerhub_username
DOCKERHUB_TOKEN=your_dockerhub_access_token

# === Production Application Secrets ===
# These override local development values in production
JWT_SECRET=your_production_jwt_secret
FRONTEND_URL=https://your-production-frontend-url.com

# === MongoDB Production (Optional) ===
# Only if using cloud MongoDB (e.g., MongoDB Atlas)
# MONGODB_URI_PROD=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/satoshifund-prod

# === AWS EC2 Deployment ===
# Required for AWS SSM deployment to EC2
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-aws-access-key
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-aws-secret-key
AWS_REGION=ap-southeast-2
EC2_INSTANCE_ID=i-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
EC2_HOST=ec2-xx-xxx-xxx-xxx.ap-southeast-2.compute.amazonaws.com

# ================================================
# How to Add Secrets to GitHub:
# ================================================
# 1. Go to your repository on GitHub
# 2. Click Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
# 3. Click "New repository secret"
# 4. Add each secret with the exact name shown above
# 5. For multi-line values (like SSH keys), paste the entire content
#
# Note: GitHub Secrets are encrypted and never exposed in logs